<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,554,974]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,435,554,578]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Description. Egg.</emphasis>
Very small size; completely silvery white and changing to snowy white before hatching. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[314,403,587,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Larva.</emphasis>
First instar is dark-pink, head and last abdominal segment dark-brown, thorax black with silver band in pronotum; Second to fifth instars similar to first, except color soft pink and length 
<quantity box="[192,337,653,677]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="7.35" valueMax="8.9" valueMin="5.8">5.8–8.9 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[355,437,653,677]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="25.[192,275,1819,1841]" captionTargetBox="[377,1254,213,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[377,1254,213,1785]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 1. Larvae of Lepidoptera pests of sapodilla. A) Dichrorampha sapodilla Heppner. B) Comotia torsicornis Dyar. C) Holcocera crassicornella Dietz. D) Zamagiria laidion (Zeller). E) Electrostrymon angelia (Hewitson). F) Phidotricha erigens Ragonot. G) Banisia myrsusalis Walker. H) Banisia argutula Whalley. I) Pyroderces badia (Hodges). J) Erinnyis ello (Linnaeus)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3676601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3676601/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,599,653,677]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Pre-pupa.</emphasis>
Similar in size and color to that of last instar but wider and paler. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,272,686,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Pupa.</emphasis>
Elongate, similar size to last larval instar. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[796,879,686,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Adult.</emphasis>
Sexually dimorphic, female larger and darker than male. 
<emphasis box="[334,501,719,742]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Wing expanse</emphasis>
: males 
<quantity box="[598,744,719,743]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="4.05" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="3.4">3.4–4.7 mm</quantity>
, females 
<quantity box="[860,1008,719,743]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="4.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="5.35" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="4.9">4.9–5.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1020,1111,719,743]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Wings.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[1119,1296,719,743]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Dorsal surface</emphasis>
: Forewings pale-brown with a series of transverse markings of different color shades ranging from dark-brown to white occasionally overlain with golden-brown or dark-gray scales. Hindwings dark-brown with overlaid with dark-gray or white scales. 
<emphasis box="[583,770,818,842]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Ventral surface</emphasis>
: Both wings dark-brown with overlaid with dark-gray or white scales. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[395,475,851,875]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Head.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[484,599,851,874]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Antennae</emphasis>
: Filiform; nearly ¾ length of the body. 
<emphasis box="[1098,1175,851,874]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Vertex</emphasis>
: Brown. 
<emphasis box="[1289,1432,850,874]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mouthparts</emphasis>
: Labial palpi with second and third segment longer than first; lines with different shades present. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1362,1440,884,908]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Body.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[192,452,916,940]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Thorax and abdomen</emphasis>
: Generally reddish-brown but sometimes pale-brown or brown blended with gray and dark-brown. 
<emphasis box="[403,458,950,973]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Legs</emphasis>
: Similar to labial palps in coloration (
<figureCitation box="[922,1014,950,974]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="26.[192,275,1790,1812]" captionTargetBox="[379,1254,213,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[379,1254,213,1756]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figure 2. Adults of Lepidoptera pests of sapodilla. The unlabeled images in the top half of the figure are to scale, whereas the labeled images in the bottom half of the figure have been resized. A) Dichrorampha sapodilla Heppner. B) Comotia torsicornis Dyar. C) Holcocera crassicornella Dietz. D) Zamagiria laidion (Zeller). E) Pyroderces badia (Hodges). F) Phidotricha erigens Ragonot. G) Banisia myrsusalis Walker. H) Banisia argutula Whalley. I) Electrostrymon angelia (Hewitson). J) Erinnyis ello (Linnaeus)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3676603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3676603/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[192,1440,998,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,371,998,1022]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodges" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[378,587,998,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Pyroderces" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[378,587,998,1022]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Pyroderces badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in the 
<collectingCountry box="[780,841,999,1023]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">USA</collectingCountry>
, mainly in 
<collectingRegion box="[978,1070,999,1023]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Florida</collectingRegion>
, but has also been reported in 
<collectingRegion box="[192,317,1032,1056]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[330,481,1032,1056]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Washington</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[495,622,1032,1056]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[635,755,1032,1056]" country="United States of America" name="Maryland" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Maryland</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[820,909,1032,1056]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hodges" box="[926,1096,1032,1056]" firstAuthor="Hodges" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" refId="ref14675" refString="Hodges, R. W. 1978. The moths of America north of Mexico, fasc. 6.1: Gelechioidea: Cosmoptergidae. E. W. Classey Ltd. and the Wedge Entomological Research Foundation; London. ix + 166 p." type="book" year="1978">Hodges, 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Adamski, D. &amp; J. W. Brown &amp; H. W. White" box="[1110,1362,1032,1056]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="341 - 346" part="108" refId="ref12318" refString="Adamski, D., J. W. Brown, and H. W. White. 2006. Description of the immature stages of Pyroderces badia (Hodges) (Lepidoptera: Cosmopterigidae), with a new host record from Louisiana. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 108: 341 - 346." title="Description of the immature stages of Pyroderces badia (Hodges) (Lepidoptera: Cosmopterigidae), with a new host record from Louisiana" type="journal article" year="2006">Adamski et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bella, S. &amp; G. Mazzeo" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino di Zoologia agraria e di Bachicoltura, Milano" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="255 - 260" part="38" refId="ref12637" refString="Bella, S., and G. Mazzeo. 2006. First record of Anatrachyntis badia (Hodges, 1962) (Lepidoptera Cosmopterigidae) in Italy. Bollettino di Zoologia agraria e di Bachicoltura, Milano, Serie II 38: 255 - 260." title="First record of Anatrachyntis badia (Hodges, 1962) (Lepidoptera Cosmopterigidae) in Italy" type="journal article" year="2006">Bella and Mazzeo 2006</bibRefCitation>
). It has also been observed in 
<collectingCountry box="[762,892,1065,1089]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(Quesada-Jiménez 2013), 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1277,1065,1089]" name="Cuba" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso, O. &amp; R. Nunez &amp; J. C. Lezcano &amp; M. Suris" journalOrPublisher="Pastos y Forrajes." pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="182 - 184" part="38" refId="ref12511" refString="Alonso, O., R. Nunez, J. C. Lezcano, and M. Suris. 2015. Ithome lassula Hodges (Lepidoptera: Cosmopterigidae), una nueva especie para Cuba asociada a Leucaena leucocephala (Lam.) de Wit. Pastos y Forrajes. 38: 182 - 184." title="Ithome lassula Hodges (Lepidoptera: Cosmopterigidae), una nueva especie para Cuba asociada a Leucaena leucocephala (Lam.) de Wit" type="journal article" year="2015">Alonso et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[273,389,1098,1122]" name="Barbados" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Barbados</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bennett, F. D. &amp; M. M. Alam" bookContentInfo="81 p." box="[403,697,1098,1122]" journalOrPublisher="Caribbean Agricultural Research and Development Institute (CARDI); Saint Augustine, Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" refId="ref12753" refString="Bennett, F. D., and M. M. Alam. 1985. An annotated check list of insects and terrestrial arthropods of Barbados. Caribbean Agricultural Research and Development Institute (CARDI); Saint Augustine, Trinidad and Tobago. 81 p." title="An annotated check list of insects and terrestrial arthropods of Barbados" type="book" year="1985">Bennett and Alam, 1985</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[763,885,1098,1122]" name="Honduras" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Honduras</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, J. Y. &amp; D. L. Matthews &amp; A. D. Warren &amp; M. A. Solis &amp; D. J. Harvey &amp; P. Gentili-Poole &amp; R. Lehman &amp; T. C. Emmel &amp; C. V. Covell, Jr." box="[898,1108,1098,1122]" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Mundi 0205" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref15798" refString="Miller, J. Y., D. L. Matthews, A. D. Warren, M. A. Solis, D. J. Harvey, P. Gentili-Poole, R. Lehman, T. C. Emmel, and C. V. Covell, Jr. 2012. An annotated list of the Lepidoptera of Honduras. Insecta Mundi 0205: 1 - 72." title="An annotated list of the Lepidoptera of Honduras" type="book chapter" year="2012">Miller et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodges" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1290,1391,1097,1121]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Pyroderces" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badia">
<emphasis box="[1290,1391,1097,1121]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">P. badia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded in nine European countries: 
<collectingCountry box="[715,803,1131,1154]" name="France" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[815,902,1131,1155]" name="Greece" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[913,974,1131,1155]" name="Italy" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1062,1131,1155]" name="Malta" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Malta</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1229,1131,1155]" name="Netherlands" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Netherlands</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1241,1350,1131,1155]" name="Portugal" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1435,1131,1155]" name="Spain" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Spain</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[291,333,1164,1187]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">UK</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Koster and Sammut" box="[347,662,1164,1188]" firstAuthor="Koster" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="49 - 63" refId="ref15243" refString="Koster, S. J. C., and P. Sammut. 2006. Faunistic notes on Momphidae, Batrachedridae, Stathmopodidae and Cosmopterigidae from the Maltese Islands. Nota lepidopterologica 29: 49 - 63." type="journal article" year="2006">Koster and Sammut 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
